In the meantime Virendra falls in love with a beautiful girl NISHA (Sonali Bendre) whose marriage was fixed by his father to a wealthy contractor's son. But the girl loves Virendra against her father's will and so starts the fight between Virendra and the girl's father supported by the contractor and his son with gang. Majorsaab helps Virendra to get his love and to change Virendra from spoilt brat to a good and brave soldier.

Title: Jugjugg Jeeyo

Kukoo's parents, Bheem and Geeta, a couple that everyone looks up to, have no plans of making Kukoo and Naina's lives easier. They have their own plans and set of surprises in store for the young couple; all this in the middle of Kukoo's sister's wedding.

Title: Shamshera

overview: Uday Gupta, a medical college student wanted to specialise in Orthopaedic, but is stuck in an all-female class of Gynaecology. Will he change his department, or will the department change him?

Title: Code Name: Tiranga
Cast: Parineeti Chopra,Harrdy Sandhu,Sharad Kelkar
overview: Tasked with capturing a wanted criminal, a fierce undercover agent wrestles with perilously high stakes when her heart is pulled into the mission.
title: Code Name: Tiranga

overview: An atheist archaeologist turned believer must race against time to prove the true existence of the legendary Ram Setu before evil forces destroy the pillar of India’s heritage.

overview: An egoistic real estate broker in huge debts, meets with an accident. As he gains consciousness, he realizes that he is in heaven. God appears before him and informs him that he must play a 'Game of Life'. If he manages to win, he will be sent back to earth; if he loses, he will be sent to hell.

overview: Sparks fly when vivacious yet sensitive Tara collides with a reclusive charmer Bilal in this slice of life story set in vibrant and diverse London.

overview: Two crazy, jobless, horror-film addicts Major and Gullu, under immense family pressure to find work, hit upon the idea to float a unique ghost-capturing service when they meet a spirit, Ragini, who makes their business a success but in return asks them for a favour which they are compelled to honour.

overview: Rajshri wants to be a sports presenter on TV but is promptly told that she is 'too healthy' for it. Saira, a fashion designer also has hit rock bottom in her life after she is cheated on by her boyfriend. A chance encounter between the two leads them to London to discover themselves and challenge the norms of who's a 'normal woman'.

He resents the noise children make while playing, as he prefers quiet and solitude. His reclusion is shattered when his neighbor, Mili, comes into his life. At first he hates the intrusion, but then grows fond, and ultimately falls in love with her. When the time comes for him to propose to this sunny, cheerful, and positive young lady, he learns that she has only a few more months to live..
title: Mili

Title: Tadka
Cast: Nana Patekar,Shriya Saran,Ali Fazal,Taapsee Pannu
overview: A middle-aged Tukaram is passionate about food and archaeology but it’s a misplaced call from Madhura that adds the tadka to his life. While love simmers, Nicole and Sidharth’s story spices up too.

Title: Rocket Gang
Cast: Aditya Seal,Nikita Dutta
overview: Five friends take a getaway trip and stay at Wonder Villa. But, the haunted villa's supernatural powers suck them in and their only chance to survive is by dancing.
title: Rocket Gang

overview: Amit, Om, Javed and Bhupen - a group of four friends - have come a long way in life. Bhupen had a lifelong dream of going to Mount Everest with his three friends but the idea is quashed immediately as soon as he expresses it to them during a get-together. However, Bhupen's sudden death leads the trio to leave their cozy Delhi lives and trek to Everest Base Camp as friendship was their only motivation.
title: Uunchai

Title: Monica, O My Darling
Cast: Rajkummar Rao,Huma Qureshi,Radhika Apte,Sikandar Kher
overview: A slick robotics expert joins a murderous plot after a passionate affair takes a sudden turn, but nothing — not even death — is what it seems to be.

Title: Thai Massage

overview: A typical middle-class 70-year-old widower, Atmaram Dubey, who has been celibate for decades, realises he will probably never have sex. This awakening catapults him into an outrageous journey of self-discovery defying societal norms.

Title: Mister Mummy
Cast: Riteish Deshmukh,Genelia Deshmukh,Mahesh Manjrekar
overview: Amol, a cranky PT teacher and his wife Gugloo have opposing choices when it comes to children but destiny has something else planned for the childhood sweethearts.
title: Mister Mummy

overview: Inspired by legendary folklore rooted in Arunachal Pradesh, Bhediya tells the story of Bhaskar, a man who gets bitten by a mythical wolf and begins to transform into the creature himself. As Bhaskar and his ragtag buddies try to find answers, he is worried that the monster in him will wipe out human existence in the local town.
title: Bhediya

Title: Qala
Cast: Tripti Dimri,Swastika Mukherjee,Babil Khan
overview: Haunted by her past, a talented singer with a rising career copes with the pressure of success, a mother's disdain and the voices of doubt within her.
title: Qala

overview: At the age of just 30, Maanav at the peak of his acting career gets caught up in a murder accusation, which turns his own life into an eccentric action thriller as he flees the country, with a vengeful politician hot on his heels.

Title: Freddy
Cast: Kartik Aaryan
overview: Introverted and awkward Dr. Freddy Ginwala desperately searches for a soulmate. When he finally finds her, the relationship becomes as painful as a root canal.
title: Freddy

Title: India Lockdown
Cast: Shweta Basu,Aahana Kumra,Prateik Babbar,Sai Tamhankar,Prakash Belawadi
overview: The Indian government announces a country-wide lockdown for 21 days due to the pandemic. India Lockdown encapsulates the story of four out of lakhs of individuals whose lives came to a standstill.
title: India Lockdown

Title: Salaam Venky
Cast: Vishal Jethwa
overview: Sujata, an ideal mother, who battles the most challenging situations one can ever face with a smile.
title: Salaam Venky

Title: Vadh
Cast: Sanjay Mishra,Neena Gupta
overview: A leading psychologist's much younger wife begins an extramarital affair with his close friend. When the doctor finds out, he plots revenge, which puts himself, his wife, his close friend and his brother in mortal danger.
title: Vadh

Title: Maarrich
Cast: Tusshar Kapoor,Naseeruddin Shah,Rahul Dev,Seerat Kapoor,Anita Hassanandani
overview: 2 brutal murders, 6 suspects and one fearless cop - Rajiv Dixit, a sharp-witted Mumbai police officer , is on a mission to track down the unidentified killer behind these murders.
title: Maarrich

Title: Josef – Born in Grace
Cast: Victor Banerjee,Subrat Dutta
overview: An adaptation of a short story "Joseph" written by Umakanta Mahapatra and is set in the foothills of the Himalayas between 1960 and 1980 in India. Father O'Hara (Victor Banerjee), a missionary doctor with the help of his caretaker Maularam (Sudarshan Juyal), raises an orphan baby Josef (Hitesh Bisht). While still a young boy, Josef is sent to Dehradun, Uttarakhand, for his studies and vocational training. Josef (Subrat Dutta) returns back with a reputation as a great cook as well as his love for alcohol. The film explores in its unfolding of time, the different paths that Father O'Hara, Josef, and Maularam take in their respective journeys for spiritual fulfillment through memories, duty, and search as well as the their interaction with friends and acquaintances. Through static mis-en-scenes, the narrative of the film reflects the all-encompassing nature of time, pre-empting and repeating itself in allegorical hues.
title: Josef - Born in Grace

Title: Blurr
Cast: Taapsee Pannu,Gulshan Devaiah
overview: With progressive blindness setting in, Gayatri has to find answers to her twin sister's unlikely death. As the lines of reality keep getting blurred, is she ready to look the truth in the eye?

Title: Govinda Naam Mera

overview: An abusive wife, a hot girlfriend and a court case, Govinda Waghmare is just not able to catch a break. The icing on top of that horrible cake - a murder.
title: Govinda Naam Mera

Title: Ajay Wardhan

overview: The biographical drama is based on Dr Ajay Aryan becoming a famed dental surgeon in Chandigarh, and follows the lead’s rise from being an impoverished goat herder in Haryana to achieving his goals. Meanwhile, his love story, break-up and reuniting with the love of his life also form an integral part of the tale.
title: Ajay Wardhan

Title: Cirkus
Cast: Ranveer Singh,Pooja Hegde,Jacqueline Fernandez,Varun Sharma
overview: Two sets of identical twins are accidentally separated at birth. Several years later, when they are coincidentally in the same town, there is a lot of confusion and misunderstanding when people mistake them for each other.

Title: Nail Polish

However, there's much more than what meets the eye in this courtroom drama that explores the uncertainty of human mind and the journey of criminal discovery.
title: Nail Polish

Title: Ramprasad Ki Tehrvi
Cast: Naseeruddin Shah,Vinay Pathak,Vikrant Massey,Konkona Sen,Vineet Kumar,Manoj Pahwa,Parambrata Chattopadhyay,Supriya Pathak,Deepika Amin,Ninad Kamat

Cast: Vinay Pathak, Manoj Pahwa, Seema Pahwa, Dolly Ahluwalia, Sabah Kapoor
overview: On hearing the news that one of the Sharma family members in Mumbai, Devendar may pass off anytime, his siblings - Jeetendar, Ravindar and Lalita, immediately rush down to be with him and his family for support, along with their families from across the country.
title: Khajoor Pe Atke

Title: Parmanu: The Story Of Pokhran
Cast: John Abraham, Diana Penty, Boman Irani
overview: A look at India's second confidential nuclear test series at Pokhran lead by Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam, during the time of PM Atal Bihari Vajpayee's tenure.
title: Parmanu: The Story of Pokhran

Title: Bioscopewala
Cast: Danny Denzongpa, Geetanjali Thapa, Tisca Chopra, Adil Hussain
overview: Based on Rabindranath Tagore’s famous short story 'Kabuliwala', the film is about a young girl’s quest to discover more about her dead father’s friend who used to play bioscope shows for her as a kid.
title: Bioscopewala

Title: Veere Di Wedding
Cast: Kareena Kapoor, Sonam Kapoor, Swara Bhaskar, Shikha Talsania, Sumeet Vyas
overview: Kalindi, Avni, Sakshi and Meera are childhood friends. Kalindi and Rishabh are getting married, and the four gal pals come together for their veere’s wedding. But of course, there can be no shaadi without showsha and a lot of drama. This wedding celebration brings out skeletons from the closet, unspoken truths and some harsh realities as well.
title: Veere Di Wedding

Title: Bhavesh Joshi Superhero
Cast: Harshvardhan Kapoor, Priyanshu Painyuli, Nishikant Kamat
overview: A young man who stands for the right discovers that he's destined to do bigger things, which will transform him from a common man into a Superhero.
title: Bhavesh Joshi Superhero

Title: Phamous
Cast: Jackie Shroff, Jimmy Sheirgill, Kay Kay Menon, Shriya Saran, Mahie Gill, Pankaj Tripathi
overview: An epic journey of love in Chambal, amongst the clash of power and the roar of guns.
title: Phamous

Title: Race 3
Cast: Anil Kapoor, Bobby Deol, Daisy Shah, Freddy Daruwala, Jacqueline Fernandez, Salman Khan, Saqib Saleem
overview: The Singh family comprises of Shamsher his step-son Sikandar, twins Suraj and Sanjana. They run a business of illegal arms and trade with the help of their friend Yash. Things get dramatic when Jessica meets Sikandar and the family ties are strained under each character’s ulterior motives.
title: Race 3

Title: Lust Stories
Director: Anurag Kashyap, Karan Johar, Zoya Akhtar, Dibakar Banerjee
Cast: Radhika Apte, Sanjay Kapoor, Kiara Advani, Vicky Kaushal, Neha Dhupia, Neil Bhoopalam, Bhumi Pednekar, Manisha Koirala, Akash Thosar
overview: An anthology of four stories that sheds light on modern relationships from the viewpoint of the Indian woman.
title: Lust Stories

Title: Sanju
Cast: Ranbir Kapoor
overview: Sanju explores some of the most crucial chapters from movie star Sanjay Dutt’s dramatic and controversial real life. It gives a lowdown on his tryst with drugs and his trials and tribulations in the Arms Acts case and the 1993 Mumbai blasts.
title: Sanju

Title: Soorma
Cast: Diljit Dosanjh, Taapsee Pannu, Angad Bedi
overview: Soorma, a comeback story of the hockey legend Sandeep Singh is a biopic that chronicles the life and times of the famed hockey player.
title: Soorma

Title: Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster 3
Cast: Sanjay Dutt, Jimmy Sheirgill, Mahi Gill, Chitrangada Singh, Soha Ali Khan
overview: It’s the third edition of Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster series where it’s survival of the wittiest and the wealthiest. Will the royal couple Madhavi Devi and Aditya Pratap Singh live to tell the tale of relentless plotting, scheming and backstabbing?
title: Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster 3

Title: Nawabzaade
Cast: Raghav Juyal, Punit Pathak, Dharmesh Yelande, Isha Rikhi
overview: Three best friends fall in love with a simple, stay-at-home girl from their neighbourhood, who (unintentionally) pits them against one another. But, as love flies out of the window, the three men realise that their beloved is more than what meets the eye
title: Nawabzaade

Title: Fanney Khan
Cast: Anil Kapoor, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Rajkummar Rao, Karan Singh Chhabra, Divya Dutta
overview: The journey of a struggling singer 'Fanney Khan' who aspires to make his daughter a big name in the music world.
title: Fanney Khan

Title: Mulk
Cast: Rishi Kapoor, Prateik Babbar, Rajat Kapoor, Taapsee Pannu, Ashutosh Rana, Manoj Pahwa,Neena Gupta
overview: The youngest son of a Muslim family settled in Benaras gets involved in terrorist activities, leading to a bomb blast massacre. His actions have an adverse effect on the family who are left to defend themselves as people who are innocent and not anti-nationals.
title: Mulk

Title: Brij Mohan Amar Rahe!
Cast: Arjun Mathur, Nidhi Singh, Vijayant Kohli, Sunny Hinduja
overview: Faking his death to escape the realities of his uneventful life worked out well for Brij Mohan -- until he was sentenced to death for his own murder.
title: Brij Mohan Amar Rahe!

Title: Laxmi and Tikli Bomb
Cast: Vibhawari Deshpande, Suchitra Pillai, Chitraganda Chakraborty, Upendra Limaye
overview: Two sex workers decide to kick men out of the system and form a cooperative that runs the business for women and by women. How do they do things differently? And how far can they get under and overarching and overbearing patriarchy?
title: Tikli and Laxmi Bomb

Title: Karwaan
Cast: Irrfan Khan, Dulquer Salman, Mithila Palkar, Kriti Kharbanda
overview: Avinash, a dejected soul stuck in a dead-end job shares a strange relationship with his father. He holds him responsible for crushing his dreams. However, he is left pondering upon this longstanding hatred when he hears of his father’s untimely demise.
title: Karwaan

Title: Gold
Cast: Akshay Kumar, Kunal Kapoor, Mouni Roy, Amit Sadh
overview: Set in 1948, the historic story of India's first Olympic medal post their independence.
title: Gold

Title: Satyameva Jayate
Cast: John Abraham, Manoj Bajpayee, Aisha Sharma, Amruta Khanvilkar
overview: DCP Shivansh has been tasked to catch Vir, the man behind police killings in the city. Both are eventually against the same enemy but divided by a fine line, the law.
title: Satyameva Jayate

Title: Genius
Cast: Utkarsh Sharma, Ishita Chauhan, Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Ayesha Jhulka
overview: An orphan, with a brilliant mind, joins RAW and is burdened by the killing of his entire team. Until he doesn't avenge their death, he can't live in peace with his love. So, he hatches a genius plan.
title: Genius

Title: Happy Phirr Bhag Jayegi
Cast: Sonakshi Sinha, Diana Penty, Ali Fazal, Jimmy Shergill, Jassi Gill
overview: Horticulture professor Happy arrives in Shanghai and the other Happy along with husband Guddu also lands up in the Chinese city at the same time. Gangsters who’ve come to kidnap Happy and her husband, pick up the wrong Happy, while Guddu and his wife Happy are escorted to a university to deliver a lecture.
title: Happy Phirr Bhag Jayegi

Title: Toba Tek Singh
Cast: Pankaj Kapur, Vinay Pathak
overview: The story takes place just before the India-Pakistan partition in one of the oldest mental asylums in undivided India. Situated in Lahore, it was home to Hindu, Muslim and Sikh patients who were left behind by their uncaring families. Friendships were thick between the patients who had nobody but each other for company. Each had a story that made for an interesting tale but none quite like Bishan Singh.
title: Toba Tek Singh

Title: Stree
Cast: Rajkummar Rao, Shraddha Kapoor, Aparshakti Khurana, Pankaj Tripathi
overview: Stree is a 1961 Indian fantasy film selected as the Indian entry for the Best Foreign Language Film at the 34th Academy Awards, but not nominated.
title: Stree

Title: Once Again
Cast: Shefali Shah, Neeraj Kabi
overview: After a chance phone call leads to daily conversations, a widowed restaurant owner and a lonely film actor plan to finally meet in person.
title: Once Again

Title: Paltan
Cast: Jackie Shroff, Sonu Sood, Arjun Rampal, Gurmeet Choudhary, Siddhanth Kapoor, Harshvardhan Rane, Luv Sinha, Esha Gupta, Monica Gill, Sonal Chauhan, Dipika Kakar, Aditii Arya Sharma
overview: A war drama based on the Indo-China War of 1962, JP Dutta's "PALTAN" focuses on the hard-hitting truth of India's relations with China, and how it is important to acknowledge that China, an enormous power in world politics, poses to be a huge threat to India.
title: Paltan

Title: Laila Majnu
Cast: Mir Sarwar, Avinash Tiwary, Tripti Dimri, Ruchika Kapoor
overview: Laila is a free-spirited girl from a conservative family who firmly believes in living for the present. Qais, a spoilt brat, falls head over heels in love with her. Their families, however, are warring over property, which leads to self-destruction, pain and bleeding hearts.
title: Laila Majnu

Title: Gali Guleiyan
Cast: Manoj Bajpayee, Ranvir Shorey, Neeraj Kabi, Shahana Goswami
overview: A reclusive Old Delhi shopkeeper, spends his time watching people through hidden cameras. When he overhears a boy being beaten, his search for the boy leads to reality crumbling around him, as he is lost in the maze of the city and his own mind.
title: Gali Guleiyan

Title: Halkaa
Cast: Ranvir Shorey, Paoli Dam, Tathastu, Kumud Mishra
overview: Halkaa is a story of a eight year old boy who lives in the slums of delhi and wants proper access to a toilet. This story is of a boy who is a real life Superhero who fights against the system to get what he wants and deserves.
title: Halkaa

Title: Manmarziyaan
Cast: Abhishek Bachchan, Vicky Kaushal, Taapsee Pannu
overview: A spirited girl finds herself caught in a complicated love triangle while burdened with societal and familial pressures.
title: Manmarziyaan

Title: Love Sonia
Cast: Mrunal Thakur, Freida Pinto, Manoj Bajpayee, Rajkummar Rao, Richa Chadda, Anupam Kher, Adil Hussain, Sai Tamhankar
overview: Inspired by a real story of young girl's journey escape from the world of international sex trafficking.
title: Love Sonia

Title: Mitron
Cast: Jackky Bhagnani, Kritika Kamra, Pratik Gandhi, Neeraj Sood
overview: Jai (Jackky Bhagnani), born and brought up with middle-class values, has a ‘take it easy’ approach to life. Since he doesn't believe in herd mentality, he and his two best friends, Raunak (Pratik Gandhi) and Deepu (Shivam Parekh) start looking for unique ways to make it big in the world. During this trial and error phase, Jai realizes his dream. But his decision of choosing an unprofitable career path doesn’t go down too well with his father (Neeraj Sood), who has bigger aspirations for him. Therefore, in order to bring stability in his life, his father decides to get him married. Destiny, however, has something else in store for Jai, when he accidentally meets Avni (Kritika Kamra), an ambitious, MBA graduate, who wants to start her own business. Set in the backdrop of the Gujarati milieu, the film traces Jai and Avni’s personal journey, as they both find themselves and discover the true meaning of friendship in the bargain.
title: Mitron

Title: Batti Gul Meter Chalu
Cast: Shahid Kapoor, Shraddha Kapoor, Divyendu Sharma, Yami Gautam
overview: The life of three friends takes a tragic turn due to an inflated electricity bill, which leads to a courtroom drama and social awakening.
title: Batti Gul Meter Chalu

Title: Manto
Cast: Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Tahir Raj Bhasin, Rasika Dugal, Rajshri Deshpande
overview: In Bombay's seedy-shiny film world, Manto and his stories are widely read and accepted. But as sectarian violence engulfs the nation, Manto makes the difficult choice of leaving his beloved Bombay. In Lahore, he finds himself bereft of friends and unable to find takers for his writings.
title: Manto

Title: Ishqeria
Cast: Neil Nitin Mukesh, Richa Chaddha
overview: Ishqeria is a story of a small town girl who falls madly in love with the most sought after guy in college. It is a journey of first love, growing up and second chances.
title: Ishqeria

Title: Sui Dhaaga
Cast: Varun Dhawan, Anushka Sharma
overview: Mauji stays in a village near Delhi with his wife Mamta, father and mother. Varun works at a shop that sells sewing machines, owned by Bansal and his son Prashant. Both have a habit of ill-treating Mauji and make him do fun antics. When Prashant gets married, Bansal invites Mauji and his entire family. Mamta feels humiliated when she sees Mauji being asked to imitate a dog by the Bansals.
title: Sui Dhaaga - Made in India

Title: Pataakha
Cast: Sanya Malhotra, Sunil Grover, Radhika Madan
overview: Based on Charan Singh Pathik's short story Do Behnein, Pataakha narrates the story of two feuding sisters who realize the true nature of their relationship only after marriage separates them.
title: Pataakha

Title: Loveyatri
Cast: Aayush Sharma, Warina Hussain
overview: Romance blossoms between young Sushrut and Michelle when they meet during the festival of Navratri. When Michelle returns home to the United Kingdom, Sushrut embarks on an adventurous journey through a strange land to win back the woman he loves.
title: Loveyatri

Title: Andhadhun
Cast: Ayushman Khurana, Tabu, Radhika Apte
overview: A series of mysterious events changes the life of a blind pianist who now must report a crime that was actually never witnessed by him.
title: Andhadhun

Title: Jalebi
Cast: Rhea Chakraborty, Digangana Suryavanshi, Varun Mitra
overview: An estranged couple happen to meet on a train journey where they independently reflect on what went wrong in their relationship and whether they will truly be able to move forward and start a new chapter, together or alone.
title: Jalebi

Title: Helicopter Eela
Cast: Kajol, Riddhi Sen, Neha Dhupia, Tota Roy Choudhury
overview: Eela, an aspiring playback singer, and single mother has given up all her dreams to raise her only son, who backlashes her for invading his privacy.
title: Helicopter Eela

Title: FryDay
Cast: Govinda, Varun Sharma
overview: What happens when an honest salesman and a flirtatious married man cross path?

column1: Chaos ensues on a Friday as one outrageously hilarious lie leads to another.

Title: Tumbbad
Cast: Soham ShahHarish Khanna, Anita Date
overview: India, 1918. On the outskirts of Tumbbad, a cursed village where it always rains, Vinayak, along with his mother and his brother, care of a mysterious old woman who keeps the secret of an ancestral treasure that Vinayak gets obsessed with.
title: Tumbbad

Title: Namaste England
Cast: Arjun Kapoor, Parineeti Chopra, Aditya Seal, Alankrita Sahai, Anil Mange, Satish Kaushik
overview: Param and Jasmeet fall in love and they get married. Their perfect romance gets disturbed by Jasmeet’s suppressed ambition however, she has dreams of going to London so that she can pursue her career and build a better life for herself. But Param unable to get a visa and that creates some high drama in their love life.
title: Namaste England

Title: Badhaai Ho
Cast: Ayushman Khurrana, Neena Gupta, Gajraj Rao, Surekha Sikri, Sanya Malhotra
overview: A 25-year-old man tries to suppress his embarrassment when his mother announces that she is pregnant.
title: Badhaai Ho

Title: Baazaar
Cast: Saif Ali Khan, Radhika Apte, Chitrangada Singh, Denzil Smith, Rohan Mehra, Sonia Balani
overview: After moving to Mumbai, an ambitious young man becomes the stock trader for a notorious businessman.
title: Baazaar

Title: 5 Weddings
Cast: Rajkummar Rao, Nargis Fakhri, Bo Derek, Candy Clark, Anneliese van der Pol, Suvinder Vicky
overview: An American journalist travels to India to cover Bollywood weddings, only to uncover a mosaic of cultural clashes, transgender tangles and lost loves with her travels culminating at a destination where the only journey is the one within.
title: 5 Weddings

Title: Kaashi in Search of Ganga
Cast: Sharman Joshi, Aishwarya Devan, Govind Namdev, Manoj Joshi, Manoj Pahwa, Akhilendra Mishra
overview: Devina a newspaper journalist from Lucknow falls in love with Kashi and things go awry when Kashi’s sister Ganga goes missing.
title: Kaashi in Search of Ganga

Title: Dassehra
Cast: Neil Nitin Mukesh, Tina Desai, Govind Namdev
overview: Honest inspector Aditi Singh and hard-boiled cop Rudra investigate a multiple suicide case. They stumble upon a darker truth revolving around the corrupt politician Yadav and Shankar. The political nexus forces Rudra to become the angry-young-man and one-man-army all rolled into one.
title: Dassehra

Title: Thugs of Hindostan
Cast: Amitabh Bachchan, Aamir Khan, Fatima Sana Shaikh, Katrina Kaif, Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub
overview: After the British company’s officer Clive takes over the kingdom of Mirza, Princess Zafira and Khudabaksh aka Azaad form a band of rebel pirates who swear to defeat the English officer and win their freedom back. The British Company in return, hire the wily thug Firangi track Azaad’s gang and thwart his plans.
title: Thugs of Hindostan

Title: Mohalla Assi
Cast: Sunny Deol, Sakshi Tanwar, Ravi Kishan, Saurabh Shukla, Mukesh Tiwari, Rajendra Gupta, Mithilesh Chaturvedi
overview: An idealist Sanskrit teacher deals with issues like commercialization of religion as things around him change and he struggles to keep up. But is he ready to pay the price?
title: Mohalla Assi

Title: Pihu
Cast: Myra Vishwakarma, Prerna Sharma
overview: The social thriller starring a two year-old baby girl. She is living in a home where the adults are going through a complicated phase. Being a toddler, she is occasionally trapped in the accidental situations.
title: Pihu

Title: Hotel Milan
Cast: Kunaal Roy Kapur, Karishma Sharma, Zeishan Quadri, Jaideep Ahlawat, Rajesh Sharma, Zakir Hussain
overview: Two friends start a hotel called Milan, a convenient destination for lovers to meet but things don't turn as planned as they are attacked by the anti-Romeo squad and political hooligans.
title: Hotel Milan

Title: Tigers
Cast: Emraan Hashmi, Khalid Abdalla, Geetanjali Thapa, Supriya Pathak
overview: Ayan, a pharmaceutical salesman in Pakistan, takes on the multinational health care corporation he works for after he realizes they knowingly marketed a baby formula that's responsible for the death of hundreds of babies everyday.
title: Tigers

Title: Bhaiaji Superhit
Cast: Sunny Deol, Preity Zinta, Ameesha Patel, Arshad Warsi, Shreyas Talpade, Evelyn Sharma
overview: A kind-hearted goon decides to get his wife back by making a film on their love story, while his arch nemesis tries to thwart his plans.
title: Bhaiaji Superhitt

Title: Rajma Chawal
Cast: Rishi Kapoor, Anirudh Tanwar, Amyra Dastur
overview: A father attempts to reconnect with his estranged son through social media, a new world for him.
title: Rajma Chawal

Title: Kedarnath
Cast: Sushant Singh Rajput, Sara Ali Khan
overview: Mansoor, a reserved and reticent Pithoo (porter), helps pilgrims make an arduous journey upwards to the temple town. His world turns around when he meets the beautiful and rebellious Mukku who draws him into a whirlwind of intense love.
title: Kedarnath

Title: Ascharyachakit!
Cast: Priyanka Bose, Vaibhav Raj Gupta, Ankit Raaj, Anangsha Biswas, Santosh Juvekar
overview: Desire and greed intertwines the lives of a Bollywood star, his chauffeur, a prostitute and her pimp in an unlikely love story.
title: Ascharya Fuck It

Title: Simmba
Cast: Ranveer Singh, Sara Ali Khan, Sonu Sood
overview: A corrupt police officer enjoys all the perks of being an immoral and unethical police officer until an event which transforms his life completely and forces him to choose the righteous path.
title: Simmba

Title: Haraamkhor
Cast: Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Shweta Tripathi
overview: When a vulnerable new student finds comfort in her brash teacher, their academic relationship takes a manipulative and troubling turn.
title: Haraamkhor

Title: Ok Jaanu
Cast: Aditya Roy Kapur, Shraddha Kapoor
overview: Adi and Tara move to Bombay to pursue their dreams. A chance meeting sparks off a heady, no strings attached romance until their careers pull them apart. Will ambition prevail over matters of the heart?
title: Ok Jaanu

Title: Coffee with D
Cast: Sunil Grover, Anjana Sukhani, Zakir Hussain, Dippanita Sharma
overview: A celebrated journalist interviews one of the world's most dreaded terrorists, "D".
title: Coffee with D

Title: Kaabil
Cast: Hrithik Roshan, Yami Gautam, Rohit Roy, Ronit Roy
overview: Rohan is a kind, happy young man who has been blind since birth and works as a voice-over artist for a living. Through friends, he meets Supriya, a working woman who is also blind, but proudly independent. The two start liking each other and get married. Rohan toughest journey starts in his quest of vengeance for Supriya's indirect murderers.
title: Kaabil

Title: Raees
Cast: Shah Rukh Khan, Mahira Khan, Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub
overview: Set in the early ’80s and ’90s in Gujarat, India, ‘Raees’ is a fictitious story of a crime lord named Raees, who builds an entire empire from scratch, and a police officer who is determined to bring him down.
title: Raees

Title: Hind Ka Napak Ko Jawab: MSG Lion Heart 2
Director: Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, Honeypreet Insan
Cast: Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, Honeypreet Insan
overview: Sher-e-Hind along with his sidekick Honey Preet Insan have infiltrated the Pakistani army where he gives them a befitting response to all their terrorist activities.
title: Hind Ka Napak Ko Jawab: MSG Lion Heart 2

Title: U, Me Aur Ghar
Cast: Omkar KapoorSimran Kaur Mundi
overview: U, Me Aur Ghar is India's first web-based feature film, launched by Web Talkies- a digital home entertainment brand. The film revolves around a live-in couple, Chitti and Mittu, who begin their journey by looking to buy a house in Mumbai.
title: U, Me Aur Ghar

Title: Running Shaadi
Cast: Taapsee Pannu, Amit Sadh
overview: Two friends, Ram Bharose and tech genius Cyberjeet, create a website that helps lovers to elope. The site is an instant hit; young couples line up for the opportunity to escape strict families and run away with the ones they love.
title: Running Shaadi

Title: The Ghazi Attack
Cast: Rana Daggubati, Taapsee Pannu, Kay Kay Menon, Atul Kulkarni
overview: India’s first underwater war film tries to decode the mystery behind the sinking of Pakistani submarine PNS Ghazi during the Indo-Pak war of 1971.
title: The Ghazi Attack

Title: Irada
Cast: Naseeruddin Shah, Arshad Warsi, Sharad Kelkar, Divya Dutta
overview: A mysterious bomb blast in a business tycoon's factory prompts the state CM to hire an NIA officer. He meets an ex-army man seeking revenge for his dead daughter and a journalist demanding justice for her slain boyfriend. Nothing is what it seems. The film raises contemporary ecological issue with lot of thrill.
title: Irada

Title: Rangoon
Cast: Kangana Ranaut, Shahid Kapoor, Saif Ali Khan
overview: Julia travels to the Indo-Burma border to perform for the troops during the World War II, on the insistence of Billimoria, her lover. She finds herself in love with Jemadar Malik, a soldier there.
title: Rangoon

Title: Wedding Anniversary
Cast: Nana Patekar, Mahie Gill, Priyanshu Chatterjee, Shruti Marathe
overview: Kahani met her Prince Charming Nirbhay in Goa for the first time and fell in love. So far their journey together has been excellent and today is their first wedding anniversary.
title: Wedding Anniversary

Title: Mona Darling
Cast: Anshuman Jha, Divya Menon, Suzanna Mukherjee, Sanjay Suri
overview: A contemporary who-dunnit, with a splash of supernatural, set in a college campus somewhere in India (a la Indian Institute Of Technology) where a few mysterious deaths occur and the only common link between the victims is that, seconds before their deaths, they all accepted a 'facebook friend request' from a certain profile page of Mona_Darling. The person behind the said page, Mona happens to be missing. Her friend, and a fellow student, Sarah recruits the help of a classmate, Wiki - a borderline sociopathic genius. This odd-couple of amateur sleuths carry on their investigation as the story leads them into unexpected corners and terrifying revelations. It's a pacy thriller, confined to limited locations on one single campus, populated by fresh, sexy, young characters that can be executed on a fairly shoestring budget. More importantly it captures the present zeitgeist of young India and its obsession with social networking.
title: Mona Darling

Title: Commando 2
Cast: Vidyut Jammwal, Adah Sharma, Esha Gupta
overview: India's most wanted Black Money agent, Vicky Chaddha, gets arrested in Malaysia and is kept in a safe house by the Malaysian authorities, along with his wife. A team of four is being sent to Malaysia to bring them to India. Apart from the growth of inter-personal relationships, the mission has quite a few twists and turns on its way. The story follows Karan as he uses his brain and brawn to recover all of the laundered black money.
title: Commando 2 -  The Black Money Trail

Title: Jeena Isi Ka Naam Hai
Cast: Arbaaz Khan, Ashutosh Rana, Himansh Kohli
overview: The film presents the naïve vulnerability of human life, the sincere saga of love and pain, and the glimpse of human emotions in raw form. So much of human nature is captured within the frames of the film, yet it takes you to the various land giving a realistic view of existence - the story traversing from a small town of Rajasthan, moving to the city of dreams - Mumbai and then goes on to the city that never sleeps - New York, ride us through interesting characters, each one with a diverse and unique character adding slice of life.
title: Jeena Isi Ka Naam Hai

Title: Badrinath Ki Dulhania
Cast: Varun Dhawan, Alia Bhatt, Sahil Vaid, Rituraj Singh
overview: Badrinath is looking for a typical bride; Vaidehi is looking for an independent life. Together they must break with tradition and redefine their role
title: Badrinath Ki Dulhania

Title: Aa Gaya Hero
Cast: Govinda, Ashutosh Rana, Murali Sharma
overview: An Ideal fearless cop becomes a nightmare for law breakers.The film revolves around a fearless cop, ACP Ravindra Varma (Govinda) who lays down a unique plan to nab the local goons by putting up a play act. He calls his technique, Abhinay Chakra. Through the film, we see him con goons and corrupt politicians into accepting their crimes by indulging them in fake situations.
title: Aa Gaya Hero

Title: Trapped
Cast: Rajkummar Rao, Geetanjali Thapa, Khushboo Upadhyay
overview: A man gets stuck in an empty high rise without food, water or electricity.
title: Trapped

Title: Mantra
Cast: Rajat Kapoor, Lushin Dubey, Kalki Koechlin, Shiv Panditt, Adil Hussain
overview: In 1991, the Government of India opened up the economy and unleashed the forces of globalization, forever changing the landscape of the country. A dozen years later, India was celebrating its emergence as a global economic super power. Set in 2004, in the midst of a nationwide 'India Shining' campaign, the film Mantra tells the intimate story of a family and its travails, and through it, the story of the New India. The protagonist of the film is Kapil Kapoor, the founder of an iconic Indian snack brand in the 'License Raj' old India. But today - in 2004 - he is fighting a losing battle against a multinational that has taken over the market. But it is not just his company that Kapil is desperately trying to save; it is also his own wife and children who are battling their own crises.
title: Mantra

Title: Machine
Cast: Mustafa Burmawalla, Kiara Advani
overview: Machine depicts the story of racing enthusiasts , who meet each other under mysterious circumstances. As their bond becomes stronger, they eventually fall in love. However, new things begin to unfold, which change their lives forever
title: Machine

Title: Phillauri
Cast: Anushka Sharma, Diljit Dosanjh, Suraj Sharma, Mehreen Pirzada
overview: A man is forced to marry a tree to ward off ill-luck that surrounds his love-life which turns into a nightmare when the tree is embodied by a spirit with an unfinished business.
title: Phillauri

Title: Bhanwarey
Cast: Shaurya Singh, Karan Thakur, Jashan Singh & Priyanka Shukla
overview: Set in the late 90s in Delhi, Bhanwarey revolves around three friends and how they accidentally get involved in wrongdoings while trying to cure their sexual problem of premature ejaculation and to solve them and eventually get trapped between the law and a couple of gangster groups.
title: Bhanwarey

Title: Anaarkali of Aarah
Cast: Swara Bhaskar
overview: Hailing from Aarah in Bihar, Anarkali is an item girl, famous for her vocals, suggestive dance moves and innuendo laden lyrics. She enjoys her stardom and revels in the lusty glances. The singer acknowledges that she is no saint and even makes peace with the hatred she evokes among civilised society but what she refuses to tolerate is being exploited in public by an influential politician.
title: Anaarkali of Aarah

Title: Naam Shabana
Cast: Taapsee Pannu, Prithviraj Sukumaran & Akshay Kumar
overview: Shabana Khan is the special agent who is entrusted the task of assassinating a deadly arms dealer by the Indian Intelligence Agencies.
title: Naam Shabana

Title: Laali Ki Shaadi Mein Laaddoo Deewana
Cast: Vivaan Shah, Akshara Haasan, Gurmeet Choudhary & Kavita Verma
overview: Laali and Ladoo get trapped in a royal wedding that takes place in Vadodara.
title: Laali Ki Shaadi Mein Laaddoo Deewana

Title: Mirza Juuliet
Cast: Darshan Kumar, Pia Bajpai & Chandan Roy Sanyal
overview: The world is full of fascination and obsessions. Different people have different desires and goals in life. For some its power, for some its money, for some its someone and for some its plain crazy love.The real question is that to what level can one rise or fall for his/her dream or aspirations. Mirza Juuliet is the story of such strong emotions like love, hatred, lust, trust, friendship, deceit, manipulation and above all a mixed confusion of all these emotions.
title: Mirza Juuliet

Title: Mukti Bhawan
Cast: Adil Hussain, Lalit Behl & Navnindra Behl
overview: An ominous dream convinces 77-year-old Dayanand Kumar that his end could be near. He takes the news to his son Rajiv, knowing he wants to breathe his last in the holy city of Varanasi and end the cycle of rebirth, by attaining salvation. Being the dutiful son he is, Rajiv is left with no choice but to drop everything and make the journey with his stubborn father. Daya and Rajiv check into Mukti Bhawan (Hotel Salvation) in Varanasi, a guesthouse devoted to people who want to die there. But as the days go by, Rajiv struggles to juggle his responsibilities back home, while Daya starts to bloom in the hotel. Rajiv gives his father a shot at salvation but as family bonds are tested, he finds himself torn, and not knowing what he must do to keep his life together.
title: Hotel Salvation

Title: Saanjh
Cast: Aditi Charak, Vishal Parpagga & Rupeshwari Sharma
overview: Saanjh marks the debut of Producer and Director, Ajay K Saklani, who, through this movie attempts to bring to the fore the lesser known Himachali language and tries to revive the almost forgotten Tankri Script. Saanjh is the first feature film to have been made and released in the Western Himalayan/ Pahari language. The serenity of village life amidst the Himalayas reaches the peak of sublimity as the visual tour is accompanied by some of the most melodious songs rendered by Mohit Chauhan and Pavithra Chari which strike the heart strings of even those who are unfamiliar with the Pahari dialect. The movie provides a perfect audio-visual setting for a beautiful confluence of the emotional journeys of a daughter, a mother and an orphaned boy as the sun sets on their lives and dusk sets in. Saanjh was the first film in Himachali dialect to be released in cinema halls across India.
title: Saanjh

Title: Begum Jaan
Cast: Vidya Balan, Ila Arun, Gauahar Khan, Sumit Nijhawan & Chunky Pandey
overview: On the eve of Independence, the chairman of the Border Commission, Sir Cyril Radcliffe decides to divide India and Pakistan into equitable halves. What the administration doesn’t account for is the line running through the middle of Begum Jaan’s brothel situated plonk on the border; with one half falling in India and the other in Pakistan.
title: Begum Jaan

Title: Noor
Cast: Sonakshi Sinha, Purab Kohli & Manish Chaudhary
overview: The jumbled up, crazy and happening life of journalist Noor takes a dramatic turn when she comes across a news breaking cover story
title: Noor

Title: Maatr
Cast: Raveena Tandon
overview: Shattered by the brutal murder of her daughter, A distraught mother takes justice into her own hands and seeks vengeance by fighting the system.
title: Maatr

Title: Mantostaan
Cast: Raghubir Yadav, Virendra Saxena & Sonal Sehgal
overview: Based on the four most controversial short stories of the legendary Urdu writer Saadat Hassan Manto, Mantostaan sheds light on the inhumane side of mankind. Set during the Indo-Pakistan partition in 1947, the movie highlights the retributive genocide between the religions, killing as many as 20,00,000 people and displacing over 14 million people.
title: Mantostaan

Title: Meri Pyaari Bindu
Cast: Ayushmann Khurrana & Parineeti Chopra
overview: Abhimanyu Roy is stuck with writer's block until he decides to re-live the memories of his childhood sweetheart Bindu who aspires to be a successful singer and struggles to give Abhi the one thing he craves - stability.
title: Meri Pyaari Bindu

Title: Sarkar 3
Cast: Amitabh Bachchan, Jackie Shroff, Amit Sadh & Yami Gautam
overview: Subhash Nagre or Sarkar, the patriarch of the most powerful family of Maharashtra, continues to hold centre-stage because of his immense clout with the masses. In this outing, the Godfather is joined by his grandson Shivaji Nagre who loves and hates his grandfather with equal intensity. Will Shivaji betray Subhash? Or will he become a prey to his grandfather’s machinations?
title: Sarkar 3

Title: Half Girlfriend
Cast: Arjun Kapoor & Shraddha Kapoor
overview: A boy meets a girl named Riya and falls in love. After struggling to convince her to be his girlfriend, she half-heartedly agrees to be his `half-girlfriend'.
title: Half Girlfriend

Title: Jattu Engineer
Director: Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, Honeypreet Insan
Cast: Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, Sukhottam Insan
overview: A teacher works hard to better a village that has poverty, unemployment, and a drug problem.
title: Jattu Engineer

Title: Hindi Medium
Cast: Irrfan Khan & Saba Qamar
overview: Mita and Raj Batra, an affluent couple from Delhi’s Chandni Chowk, are grappling with getting their daughter admission into an English medium school. But there is one big problem. Their zubaan is Hindi, and the elitist snobs won’t let the Hindi speaking hoi-polloi fit in.
title: Hindi Medium

Title: Sachin: A Billion Dreams
Cast: Sachin Tendulkar
overview: Sachin Tendulkar plays himself in this sports-docudrama that traces the life and times of one of the world’s biggest cricket phenomenas.​
title: Sachin: A Billion Dreams

Title: Thodi Thodi Si Manmaaniyan
Cast: Arsh Sehrawat, Shrenu Parikh, Shilpa Tulaskar & Mukesh Tiwari
overview: Siddharth, a young boy is brought up by his single mother with dreams of settling abroad. Being a part of a rock band "Antriksha"; Siddharth participates in a contest which changes his life completely. Not only that, he meets Neha - a folk singer and a social activist and gets smitten by her ideologies. In the midst of all this, he comes face to face with his father's death. Will Siddharth be able to come across the truth? Will he realize his passion, discover himself or will his mother convince him to let go off his past?
title: Thodi Thodi Si Manmaaniyan

Title: A Death in the Gunj
Cast: Vikrant Massey, Ranvir Shorey, Kalki Koechlin, Tillotama Shome, Gulshan Devaiah, Tanuja, Om Puri, Jim Sarbh, Arya Mitra Sharma
overview: A sensitive university student unraveling while on a week-long vacation with a crowd of cocksure relatives and family friends.
title: A Death in the Gunj

Title: Hanuman: Da' Damdaar
Cast: Salman Khan, Raveena Tandon & Kunal Khemu
overview: Anjani has not forgotten how her son almost lost his life. Now to protect him, she shelters him in abid to keep him from harming himself again. She doesn't even allow him to go out of the house. When his father Senapati Kesari returns from war, he is upset to find that his brave son has become a scared little boy. Maruti feels bad that his father isn't proud of him, and prays to God to make him the bravest kid in the world.  God answers his prayers and leads Maruti into a series of jungle adventures. His experiences and new friends lead him to metamorphose from a Bhola-Bhala Bajrangi to HANUMAN DA DAMDAAR!
title: Hanuman Da Damdaar

Title: Sweetiee Weds NRI
Cast: Himansh Kohli, Zoya Afroz & Darshan Jariwala
overview: Sweetiee Weds NRI is a Bollywood comedy movie, directed by Hasnain Hyderabadawala and Written by Creative Director Tariq Mohammad. The movie stars Himansh Kohli, Zoya Afroz, Darshan Jariwalla and Kiran Joneja in lead roles.
title: Sweetiee Weds NRI

Title: Dobaara: See Your Evil
Cast: Huma Qureshi & Saqib Saleem
overview: An official adaptation of the cult horror film Oculus. The film revolves around a haunted mirror. It shows the emotional journey of siblings Natasha Merchant played by Huma Qureshi and Kabeer Merchant played by Saqib Saleem dealing with the death of their parents.
title: Dobaara: See Your Evil

Title: Flat 211
Cast: Jayesh Raj & Sonal Singh
overview: Flat 211 is Latest Bollywood Crime Mystery Thriller Film directed By Sunil Sanjan,The star cast of the Film Jayesh Raj, Samonica Shrivastava, Digvijay Singh
title: Flat 211

Title: Dear Maya
Cast: Manisha Koirala
overview: Anna and Ira prank a local woman by writing her letters from a secret admirer. The prank takes a more serious turn when the local women goes missing,
title: Dear Maya

Title: Raabta
Cast: Sushant Singh Rajput, Kriti Sanon & Jim Sarbh
overview: An inseparable couple Saira and Shiva find themselves in a complicated situation when a stranger claims to be her reincarnated lover from their previous lifetime, hellbent on destroying their relationship and winning her back.
title: Raabta

Title: Behen Hogi Teri
Cast: Rajkummar Rao & Shruti Haasan
overview: Owing to the condition that the girls of the neighborhood should be treated like one's own sister, Gattu works to capture Binny's heart and the approval of his community.
title: Behen Hogi Teri

Title: Love You Family
Cast: Salman Yusuff Khan, Aksha Pardasany & Shakti Kapoor
overview: The Devani family's happiness comes crashing down when their young daughter, Khushi, marries her dance instructor, Raj, without their approval. Soon, Khushi begins to realize Raj's true colors.
title: Love You Family

Title: G Kutta Se
Cast: Rajbeer Singh & Neha Chauhan
overview: In a small village not too far from Delhi, three lives explode around taboos of love and lust. Diksha, still just a girl, is caught unguarded on camera, besmirching the "honor" of her parents. Kiran, in love with the wrong boy, becomes the target of another man's lustful vengeance, "dishonoring" her family. And Virender, a young man cruising the streets at will, enjoys all the acts society forbids women, protecting or destroying their "honor" as he wills. Set in the badlands of Haryana, known for high rates of female feticide, G explores the murky world of sexual transgression and honor killings in India.
title: G Kutta Se

Title: Bank Chor
Cast: Riteish Deshmukh, Vivek Oberoi & Rhea Chakraborty
overview: A comic-caper, that tells the story of 3 morons trying to rob a bank who pick the worst day possible when everything that can go wrong, goes wrong and how they're inadvertently caught in the crossfire.
title: Bank Chor

Title: Tubelight
Cast: Salman Khan, Sohail Khan & Zhu Zhu
overview: Laxman Singh Bisht is nicknamed tube light by his neighbours because he is feeble-minded. Despite being special, Laxman lives by one life-lesson; keep your faith alive and you can do almost anything, even stop a war.
title: Tubelight

Title: Ek Haseena Thi Ek Deewana Tha
Cast: Shiv Darshan, Natasha Fernandez & Upen Patel
overview: Natasha and her fiance, Sunny visit her ancestral property where she meets Devdhar, a man who she forms a passionate connection with.
title: Ek Haseena Thi Ek Deewana Tha

Title: Guest iin London
Cast: Kartik Aaryan, Kriti Kharbanda, Paresh Rawal & Tanvi Azmi
overview: A young couple in London struggle to live with their estranged aunt and uncle, who overstay their welcome.
title: Guest iin London

Title: Jagga Jasoos
Cast: Ranbir Kapoor & Katrina Kaif
overview: A gifted teenage detective searches for his missing father with his ladylove assistant.
title: Jagga Jasoos

Title: Shab
Cast: Raveena Tandon, Sanjay Suri, Ashish Bisht, Arpita Pal, Simon Frenay, Raj Suri, Gaurav Nanda
overview: Shab is a story that revolves around multiple characters' search for happiness and love in a complex, unforgiving, and cold city.
title: Night

Title: Lipstick Under My Burkha
Cast: Konkona Sen Sharma, Ratna Pathak Shah & Aahana Kumra
overview: Four ordinary women, inflicted by silly societal norms, have to steal, lie, cheat and hide in order to lead the lives that they rightfully deserve.
title: Lipstick Under My Burkha

Title: Munna Michael
Cast: Tiger Shroff, Nawazuddin Siddiqui & Nidhi Agerwal
overview: An expert dancer Munna who idolizes the king of pop, reluctantly tutors a gangster until their developing bond gets disrupted by their common romantic interest towards the same woman.
title: Munna Michael

Title: Indu Sarkar
Cast: Anupam Kher, Neil Nitin Mukesh, Kirti Kulhari, Tota Roy Chowdhury, Supriya Vinod, Sheeba Chaddha, Parvin Dabas
overview: Indu’s husband, a government employee, believes in using the state of Emergency to advance his career, but a moral and ideological discrepancy sets her on a own path.
title: Indu Sarkar

Title: Mubarakan
Cast: Anil Kapoor, Arjun Kapoor, Ileana D'Cruz, Neha Sharma & Athiya Shetty
overview: Singleton Kartar Singh is left with the responsibility of raising his two orphaned nephews. He asks his brother in Punjab to raise Charan and his sister in London to raise Karan. When the twins cross continents, they leave behind a trail of confusion.
title: Mubarakan

Title: Gurgaon
Cast: Akshay Oberoi, Ragini Khanna, Pankaj Tripathi, Aamir Bashir, Shalini Vatsa, Srinivas Sunderrajan
overview: A real estate baron Kehri Singh manages 'Preet Real Estate' which he runs in his daughter's name whom he consider's to be his lucky mascot. A sidelined and insulted Nikki Singh is ignored by his father and is considered to be insolent, useless and unlucky. In order to pay off a huge debt to a local criminal, Nikki sets off a chilling event that forces his father to revisit his dark past and confront a brutal truth.
title: Gurgaon

Title: Jab Harry Met Sejal
Cast: Shah Rukh Khan, Anushka Sharma, Evelyn Sharma & Chandan Roy Sanyal
overview: Haunted by the memories of home he once knew, a middle-aged tour guide unconsciously embarks on a journey to find self.
title: Jab Harry Met Sejal

Title: Toilet: Ek Prem Katha
Cast: Akshay Kumar, Bhumi Pednekar, Divyendu Sharma, Anupam Kher, Sana Khan
overview: A woman threatens to leave her husband unless he installs a toilet in their home. To win back her love and respect, he heads out on a journey to fight against the backward society.
title: Toilet: A Love Story

Title: Bareilly Ki Barfi
Cast: Ayushmann Khurrana, Rajkummar Rao, Kriti Sanon
overview: Bitti Mishra is a bohemian Bareilly girl who falls deeply in love with Pritam Vidrohi, an author because she admires his progressive way of thinking. Finding him though proves to be as hard as looking for a needle in the haystack. So Bitti seeks the help of the local printing press-owner, Chirag Dubey on her journey of love.
title: Bareilly Ki Barfi

Title: A Gentleman
Cast: Sidharth Malhotra, Jacqueline Fernandez, Darshan Kumar, Suniel Shetty
overview: Gaurav dreams of settling down with Kavya, the woman of his dreams, but she prefers a man who's more adventurous and willing to take risks. He soon stands to lose everything when a case of mistaken identity rocks his once-happy life.
title: A Gentleman

Title: Qaidi Band
Cast: Aadar Jain, Anya Singh, Sachin, Prince Parvinder Singh
overview: A riveting tale of undertrials who are brought together to form a band in jail for a social event. As their popularity grows through social media, they use their music to protest against jail authorities & the Indian judicial system. Eventually, when all hope fades, music becomes their only hope but will it set them free?
title: Qaidi Band

Title: Sniff
Cast: Khushmeet Gill, Monica Sehgal, Vijay Patkar
overview: An eight-year-old Sunny Gill has always had a blocked nose, and therefore, no sense of smell. A freak accident gives Sunny the most refined sense of smell ever. The entire dog squad of the country's police force cannot sniff what he can. But is that enough for Sunny and his young pals Google and Twitter to combat a menacing & ruthless gang of car thieves? What starts out with tracing a single missing car in the housing society, ends up busting the heftiest car racket in the country. No villain could ever be as unlikely. But then, neither could the gang of detectives!
title: Sniff!!!

Title: Baadshaho
Cast: Ajay Devgn, Emraan Hashmi, Vidyut Jammwal, Ileana D'Cruz, Esha Gupta, Sanjay Mishra, Sunny Leone Guest appearance in song, Sharad Kelkar, Ravi Kale
overview: Emergency has been declared in India. Maharani Gitanjali from one of Rajasthan's princely states has already lost her privy purse. Now, she fears that she will lose the last treasure chest of gold which has been forcibly taken away from her. So she asks her trusted lieutenant, Bhawani to step in and plan a heist.
title: Baadshaho

Title: Poster Boys
Cast: Sunny Deol, Shreyas Talpade, Bobby Deol, Sonali Kulkarni, Randheer Rai, Dilip Prabhavalkar, Elli AvrRam Special Appearance In A Song, Samiksha Bhatnagar, Bharati Achrekar
overview: Life of three men comes in trouble when their photos appear on advertisement for sterilization.
title: Poster Boys

Title: Daddy
Cast: Arjun Rampal, Aishwarya Rajesh, Nishikant Kamat, Anand Ingale, Rajesh Shringarpure, Purnanand Wandekar, Anupriya Goenka, Shruti Bapna, Usha Naik, Shrikant Yadav, Deepak Damle, Raj Arjun, Vijay Sanap, Abhimanyu Arun
overview: This is the gritty and sensational true story of Arun Gulab Gawli, a mill worker’s son who grew up in Mumbai’s impoverished Dagdi Chawl, to become an infamous don, politician and chief rival of the most powerful crime boss of the day, Dawood Ibrahim. Daddy realistically charts Mumbai’s true crime history from the 1970s and 1980s until 2012, when Gawli was finally sentenced to life imprisonment.
title: Daddy

Title: Simran
Cast: Kangana Ranaut, Sohum Shah, Hiten Kumar, Kishori Shahane, Rupinder Nagra
overview: A Gujarati housekeeper working in the United States, allows her ambitions to overpower her which leads her to get involved in the world of crime.
title: Simran

Title: Lucknow Central
Cast: Farhan Akhtar, Diana Penty, Deepak Dobriyal, Gippy Grewal, Ronit Roy, Inaamulhaq, Rajesh Sharma
overview: After being accused of murder and awaiting his death penalty, Kishen Mohan Girhotra is compelled by NGO worker Gayatri Kashyap to form a musical band of prisoners to compete at band competition held at the dreaded jail of ‘Lucknow Central’. Kishen befriends and convinces a talented bunch of criminals to form a band that provides them with a purpose and a new lease of life.
title: Lucknow Central

Title: Patel Ki Punjabi Shaadi
Cast: Rishi Kapoor, Paresh Rawal, Vir Das, Prem Chopra, Payal Ghosh, Jinal Belani, Divya Seth, Bharati Achrekar, Tiku Talsania
overview: Comedy movie is about a Punjabi and Gujarati family. and their cultural clash. Gujarati is played by Paresh Rawal and Punjabi Played by Rishi Kapoor.
title: Patel Ki Punjabi Shaadi

Title: Newton
Cast: Rajkummar Rao, Pankaj Tripathi, Anjali Patil, Raghuvir Yadav
overview: A government clerk on election duty in a conflict-ridden jungle of Central India tries his best to conduct free and fair voting despite the apathy of security forces and the looming fear of guerrilla attacks by communist rebels.
title: Newton

Title: Bhoomi
Cast: Sanjay Dutt, Aditi Rao Hydari, Sidhant Gupta
overview: A shoe-smith Arun Sachdeva (Sanjay) is shattered when he discovers that his daughter, Bhoomi (Aditi) has been raped by Dhauli (Sharad) and his gang of three. The father and daughter grieve for a bit before planning revenge.
title: Bhoomi

Title: The Final Exit
Cast: Kunaal Roy Kapur, Archana Shastry, Elena Kazan, Reyhna Malhotra, Scarlett Wilson
overview: Fashion photographer, Vidyut Sehgal has several distractions in his life, namely drugs, alcohol and women. He is also deeply troubled by his dreams in which he sees a mysterious woman posing around a strange shrine. Soon, the woman enters his bedroom and an entity seems to be sending him videos that seem to call him out to the place he has been seeing. His friend suggests he see a doctor, who advises him to abstain from substances. But when none of it helps, he decides to follow a marker sent to him on his phone and reach the mysterious place of his dreams.
title: The Final Exit

Title: JD
Cast: Govind Namdev, Aman Verma, Vedita Pratap Singh, Lalit Bisht, Arvind Gaur
overview: Based on the life and hardships faced by a journalist JD. He faced rape charges from his fellow journalist. Film also shows how politician use media for their own benefit.
title: J.D.

Title: Haseena Parkar
Cast: Shraddha Kapoor, Sharman Joshi, Siddhanth Kapoor, Rajesh Tailang, Satendra Bagasi, Ankur Bhatia
overview: Haseena is very close to her brother Dawood, who turns to a life of crime and rises to power in the Mumbai underworld. After the bomb blasts of 1993, Dawood escapes to Dubai and she falls in trouble.
title: Haseena Parkar

Title: Judwaa 2
Cast: Varun Dhawan, Jacqueline Fernandez, Vikas Verma, Taapsee Pannu, Anupam Kher, Sachin Khedekar, Upasana Singh, Rajpal Yadav, Pavan Malhotra, Ali Asgar, Vivan Bhatena, Johnny Lever, Rajat Rawail, Salman Khan (cameo)
overview: Separated at birth and peculiarly connected via their reflexes, twins Prem and Raja are reunited with each other as they set out to take down the underground smuggling world.
title: Judwaa 2

Title: ISIS: Enemies of Humanity
Cast: Yuvraj Kumar, Harish Bhimani, Rasheed Naz, Rahul Dev
overview: ISIS Enemies Of Humanity is a film based on terrorism.The Film shows in detail functioning of ISIS which is a terrorist group playing havoc all across the globe.It exposes the commander of ISIS camp who indoctrinate the youth for violent acts of terror in the form of Armed Jihad, Sleeper cells, Suicide bombers and Lone wolf attackers.The film counters this violent ideology and provides a practical peaceful solution.
title: ISIS: Enemies of Humanity

Title: Tu Hai Mera Sunday
Cast: Barun Sobti & Vishal Malhotra
overview: Five friends struggle to find a place to play football in Mumbai.
title: You Are My Sunday

Title: Chef
Cast: Saif Ali Khan, Padmapriya Janakiraman & Dhanish Karthik
overview: Roshan Kalra is a three-star Michelin chef who gets fired from New York's Gulli restaurant after he punches a customer. Forced to take a break, he flies to Kochi to spend time with his son, Armaan and his estranged wife Radha Menon. It's a fruitful trip because he manages to mend broken family ties. In a bid to help him get his mojo back, his wife suggests he put up his own food truck and begin afresh.
title: Chef

Title: Ranchi Diaries
Cast: Jimmy Sheirgill, Taaha Shah & Himansh Kohli
overview: An aspiring model Gudiya from a small town 'Ranchi' wishes to make it big in the industry, but ends up capturing the unwanted attention of a mafia leader which forces her to run away for survival with her childhood lover Manish. The following set of events pushes them to plan for an amateur bank heist with her gang of friends that goes terribly wrong.
title: Ranchi Diaries

Title: Secret Superstar
Cast: Zaira Wasim, Meher Vij & Aamir Khan
overview: A talented teenage singer-songwriter living amid domestic abuse becomes a YouTube sensation after a video in which she hides her identity goes viral.
title: Secret Superstar

Title: Golmaal Again
Cast: Ajay Devgn, Parineeti Chopra, Tabu, Arshad Warsi, Tusshar Kapoor, Shreyas Talpade, Kunal Khemu, Prakash Raj, Rohit KaduDeshmukh and Neil Nitin Mukesh
overview: Gopal and his best friends are back again, and this time they move back to their old neighborhood in a new palatial house where they learn that it is being haunted by a ghost.
title: Golmaal Again

Title: Jia aur Jia
Cast: Kalki Koechlin, Richa Chaddha
overview: A story about two starkly different women that share the same name. Together, they embark on a life-changing journey heading towards the same fate.
title: Jia aur Jia

Title: Rukh
Cast: Manoj Bajpayee, Smita Tambe, Kumud Mishra, Adarsh Gourav
overview: Away from home in a boarding school, 18-year-old Dhruv is ignorant about the ongoing crisis in his family. His life takes an unexpected turn as he gets the news of his father’s death in a car accident. As he copes with the tragedy, hidden truths begin to unravel. Even as his mother Nandini struggles to shield him, Dhruv starts looking for answers. Was his father's death an accident or a premeditated murder? The search leads to a series of unexpected revelations, as he discovers the shades of his father’s personality he had never seen before.
title: Rukh

Title: Ittefaq
Cast: Sidharth Malhotra, Sonakshi Sinha & Akshaye Khanna
overview: Taking place almost entirely over the course of one stormy night, a woman is terrified when an accused murderer escapes from a mental hospital and seeks refuge in her home.
title: Ittefaq

Title: Ribbon
Cast: Kalki Koechlin, Sumeet Vyas, Hitesh Malhan
overview: A young working urban couple is overwhelmed with the birth of a baby girl but parenthood has its own challenges.
title: Ribbon

Title: Shaadi Mein Zaroor Aana
Cast: Rajkummar Rao, Kriti Kharbanda
overview: Satyendra aka Sattu and Aarti meet for a proposed arranged marriage and fall in love in the process. On the night of their marriage, an unexpected turn of events turns their world upside down. Set in the backdrop of India's civil services, Shaadi Mein Zaroor Aana explores the challenges that Satyendra and Aarti face as a middle-class couple in India.
title: Shaadi Mein Zaroor Aana

Title: Qarib Qarib Singlle
Cast: Irrfan Khan, Parvathy, Brijendra Kala
overview: Yogi and Jaya, who have polar opposite personalities and sensibilities, meet via an online dating app. This encounter turns into so much more when the two travel to Rishikesh.
title: Qarib Qarib Singlle

Title: Aksar 2
Cast: Zareen Khan, Gautam Rode, Abhinav Shukla, Mohit Madaan
overview: A love triangle where everybody is blackmailing the other two gets a nasty upset when one of them is suddenly found murdered.
title: Aksar 2

Title: Panchlait
Cast: Amitosh Nagpal, Anuradha Mukherjee & Yashpal Sharma
overview: Set in either the 1950s or 1960s, Panchlait tells the story of a small village in North India that still has no electricity and its people live in darkness, engrossed in its own little sorrows and joys. Godhan, who belongs to the Mahato Tola of the village, is outcast from the village after he refuses to pay any part of his inheritance to the village and is falsely accused by Munri's mother for singing inappropriate Hindi songs for Munri. However, the day that the tola decides to celebrate by bringing in their own panchlight, the sarpanch realizes that no one from the tola apart from Godhan knows how to light the petromax. Keeping aside his ego, the Sarpanch annuls Gordhan's punishment and sends a word for him, who finally becomes a part of the tola and also helps the village in being lit up, becoming the hero in everyone's eyes.
title: Panchlait

Title: Tumhari Sulu
Cast: Vidya Balan & Manav Kaul
overview: A happy-go-lucky Mumbai suburban housewife Sulochana, fondly known as Sulu, lands the role of a night RJ, resulting in drastic changes to her routine life.
title: Tumhari Sulu

Title: Dil Jo Na Keh Saka
Cast: Himansh Kohli, Priya Banerjee
overview: Starring Himansh Kohli and Priya Banerjee, a romantic drama that follows the story of two childhood friends who end up going separate ways to follow their dreams. Eventually, they return to their hometown where they chance across each other and soon discover that there is more to their relationship than just friendship.
title: Dil Jo Na Keh Saka

Title: A Daughter's Tale Pankh
Cast: Nishigandha Wad, Mehul Buch, Sudhir Pandey
overview: Vidya moves out of her house after she is asked by her family to abort her child. Years later, one of her daughters who grows up to be a lawyer, decides to fight a case against her own father.
title: A Daughter's Tale PANKH

Title: Julie 2
Cast: Raai Laxmi, Ravi Kishan & Aditya Srivastava
overview: Julie, a simpleton, follows through with her dream of becoming an actress and rises to stardom. However, she is soon introduced to the murky waters of the entertainment industry. She begins to compromise on her choices and seeks love from the men in her life. Just as she decides to change paths, she is offered a political biopic that further complicates her life.
title: Julie 2

Title: Ajji
Cast: Sudhir Pandey, Sushma Deshpande
overview: After her 10-year-old granddaughter Manda is brutally raped by a serial sex offender, the young girl's Ajji sets out to seek revenge, after custodians of law refuse to bring the rapist to book, thanks to his influential political background.
title: Ajji

Title: Kadvi Hawa
Cast: Sanjay Mishra, Ranvir Shorey, Tillotama Shome, Bupesh Singh, Ekta Sawant
overview: In a village affected by climate change and scanty rainfall, a blind farmer strikes a deal with the debt recovery agent to save his son from a debt trap.
title: Kadvi Hawa

Title: Tera Intezaar
Cast: Arbaaz Khan & Sunny Leone
overview: Tera Intezaar (English: I'm waiting for you) Veer is a gifted yet undiscovered painter. Serendipity brings him next to Rounak, an art gallery owner. Upon seeing his paintings and interacting with him, Rounak falls in love with Veer. However, when she introduces Veer to some of her clients, Veer mysteriously disappears. Unable to cope with the loss, Rounak sets out to uncover the truth.
title: Tera Intezaar

Title: Firangi
Cast: Kapil Sharma, Varun Badola & Edward Sonnenblick
overview: Firangi is a Hindi movie starring Kapil Sharma and Ishita Dutta in prominent roles. Set in 1920, it is a period drama directed by Rajeev Dhingra, with Kapil Sharma as the producer, forming part of the crew.
title: Firangi

Title: Sallu Ki Shaadi
Cast: Zeenat Aman, Kiran Kumar, Asrani, Kshayp, Arshin and Sandeep Anand
overview: Sallu ki Shaadi is an upcoming Indian romantic & action film directed by Mohammad Israr Ansari.The film stars Kashyap, Arshin Mehta, Zeenat Aman and Asrani, Razak Khan, Kiran Kumar in supporting roles. The film is dedicated to actor Salman Khan.
title: Sallu Ki Shaadi

Title: Monsoon Shootout
Cast: Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Vijay Varma & Tannishtha Chatterjee
overview: A rookie cop joins the crime branch of the Mumbai police department, and on his first assignment is faced with the dilemma of whether he should shoot a murder suspect who is attempting to escape or not.
title: Monsoon Shootout

Title: Tiger Zinda Hai
Cast: Salman Khan & Katrina Kaif
overview: When a group of Indian and Pakistani nurses are held hostage in Iraq by a terrorist organization, a secret agent is drawn out of hiding to rescue them.
title: Tiger Zinda Hai

Title: Wazir
Cast: Amitabh Bachchan, Farhan Akhtar, Aditi Rao Hydari, Manav Kaul, Neil Nitin Mukesh, John Abraham, Murali Sharma, Avtar Gill
overview: 'Wazir' is a tale of two unlikely friends, a wheelchair-bound chess grandmaster and a brave ATS officer. Brought together by grief and a strange twist of fate, the two men decide to help each other win the biggest games of their lives. But there's a mysterious, dangerous opponent lurking in the shadows, who is all set to checkmate them.
title: Wazir

Title: Chalk n Duster
Cast: Shabana Azmi, Juhi Chawla, Divya Dutta, Zarina Wahab, Jackie Shroff, Arya Babbar, Richa Chadha
overview: Chalk n Duster is an emotional journey of two teachers Vidya ( Shabana Azmi) & Jyoti ( Juhi Chawla) , serving at a Mumbai - based High School. Their passion and love for teaching, bonds them in a special relationship with their students. Their gratification is good grades, moral values they strive to impart to students
title: Chalk N Duster

Title: Rebellious Flower
Cast: Prince Shah, Shashank Singh, Mantra Mugdha, Kirti Adarkar, Bachchan Pachera, Shaneel Sinha
overview: The film on the life of guru Osho Rajneesh and his spiritual journey to enlightenment.
title: Rebellious Flower

Title: Airlift
Cast: Akshay Kumar, Nimrat Kaur, Purab Kohli, Ferena Wazeir, Gunjan Malhotra
overview: When Iraq invades Kuwait in August, 1990, a callous Indian businessman becomes the spokesperson for more than 170,000 stranded countrymen.
title: Airlift

Title: Jugni
Cast: Sugandha Garg, Siddhant Behl, Sadhana Singh, Anuritta K Jha, Samir Sharma
overview: Jugni (Firefly) is the beat of the soul, the free-flying spirit. Jugni is Vibhavari (Vibs). Vibs is a music director, working on her first big break in the Hindi film industry. When work and home affairs, with her live-in boyfriend Sid hit a high tide, Vibs hits the road with a glint of hope; to find music. The journey takes her to a village in Punjab in the search of a Bibi Saroop, whose voice holds the promise that Vibs is searching for. But as the twist of fate would have it, Mastana, Bibi's son and a proficient singer himself, is the voice and man who winds his way into Vibs' heart. From here on, Jugni is about striking balances, making tough decisions while trying to soften the blows and dealing with the studied dramatic turns and unpredictabilities of life and finding the place which one can call home; home of the heart, where the firefly is at her brightest.
title: Jugni

Title: Kyaa Kool Hain Hum 3
Cast: Tushar Kapoor, Aftab Shivdasani, Mandana Karimi, Meghna Naidu, Darshan Jariwala, Krushna Abhishek, Claudia Ciesla, Riteish Deshmukh, Gizele Thakral, VJ Andy, Danny Saru
overview: In order to impress his girlfriend's conservative father, a porn actor uses his fellow adult movie stars in creating a fake traditional family.
title: Kyaa Kool Hain Hum 3

Title: Mastizaade
Cast: Tushar Kapoor, Vir Das, Sunny Leone, Shaad Randhawa, Riteish Deshmukh, Gizele Thakral, Bruna Abdullah
overview: Two womanizing bachelors fall in love with twin sisters who run a sex addiction clinic.
title: Mastizaade

Title: Sanam Teri Kasam
Cast: Mawra Hocane, Harshvardhan Rane, Anurag Sinha, Shraddha Das
overview: A musical romantic movie exploring the journey that ensues when the blue blooded boy Inder, "Who wanted to love no one" crosses paths with Saru, "Whom no one wanted to love". All their lives they were waiting to meet, but they just didn't know it . A musical tale of love , longing and loss. Sanam Teri Kasam - A Love story sealed with a Curse.
title: Sanam Teri Kasam

Title: Ghayal: Once Again
Cast: Sunny Deol, Soha Ali Khan, Aanchal Munjal, Daina Khan, Shivam Patil, Rishabh Arora, Abhilash Kumar
overview: Ajay Mehra (from previous Ghayal-1990), after finishing off his life sentence, starts a newspaper called Satyakam. Still dealing with the haunting trauma of losing his loved ones, Ajay manages to make a credible name for himself in investigative journalism. Working with a strange team of RTI activists, ex-criminals and ilk; and even stranger ways of unearthing and presenting truth, Ajay Mehra has earned quite a fan following among the youths, who finds his fearless and unforgiving approach in dealing with all kinds of sociopaths very inspiring.
title: Ghayal Once Again

Title: Fitoor
Cast: Aditya Roy Kapoor, Katrina Kaif, Tabu, Ajay Devgn, Aditi Rao Hydari, Akshay Oberoi, Lara Dutta, Rahul Bhatt
overview: A young artist tries to win the heart of his muse, while her mother hatches a scheme to end his quest for true love.
title: Fitoor

Title: Sanam Re
Cast: Pulkit Samrat, Yami Gautam, Urvashi Rautela, Rishi Kapoor, Bharti Singh, Shreyas Pardiwalla
overview: A story about the man who is confused with his love life finds solace in his birthplace with his childhood love.
title: Sanam Re

Title: Direct Ishq
Cast: Rajneesh Duggal, Nidhi Subbaiah, Arjun Bijlani
overview: Direct Ishq is a love triangle where Dolly Pandey is the common love interest of Kabeer Bajpai an event organiser and Vicky Shukla President of Kashi Vidyapeeth.
title: Direct Ishq

Title: LoveShhuda
Cast: Girish Kumar, Navneet Kaur Dhillon, Benaf Dadachandji, Yash Pandit
overview: For Gaurav Mehra and Pooja Misra, it could well have been a one-night stand which was a moment to remember, only to be erased over a period of time. However, when there is a lot more to it with dancing, talking and making merry accompanied by drinking, partying and making love, a connect is bound to be formed. A connect, which is subconscious, only to be realized when destiny has its own games to play! They are happy and content as individuals. But together they are happier, more at peace. They believe that they have already found love in respective lives. Together, they realize that this intense love they have for each other is something very different. Gaurav and Pooja may not be hunting for love as they truly feel that they have it all. But can one truly ignore the signs of something special that bonds the two together?
title: LoveShhuda

Title: Neerja
Cast: Sonam Kapoor, Shabana Azmi, Shekhar Ravjiani
overview: Neerja is a portrayal on the life of the courageous Neerja Bhanot, who sacrificed her life while protecting the lives of 359 passengers on the Pan Am flight 73 in 1986. The flight was hijacked by a terrorist organization.
title: Neerja

Title: Dhara 302
Cast: Rufy Khan, Dipti Dhotre, Gulshan Pandey
overview: Dhara 302 is a story about a young lad Veer Singh who accidentally walks on the path of crime from the age of 12. Circumstances force him to continue walking on this path and he ends up becoming a bigger criminal. However, his lady loves Kalpana makes him choose the right path. But does he manage to live a happy life? Will the society accept a person with a criminal past? All such questions are answered through the storyline.
title: Dhara 302

Title: Aligarh
Cast: Manoj Bajpayee, Rajkummar Rao
overview: Set in the city of Uttar Pradesh and based on true events, the plot revolves around Dr Shrinivas Ramchandra Siras who taught Marathi at Aligarh Muslim University. He was sacked from his position of Reader and Chair of Modern Indian Languages, on charges of homosexuality. A sting operation was conducted by a TV channel which showed him in an embrace with a rickshaw puller, at his house inside the campus.
title: Aligarh

Title: Bollywood Diaries
Cast: Raima Sen, Ashish Vidyarthi, Salim Diwan, Karuna Pandey, Vineet Kumar Singh
overview: The passionate journey of three Bollywood fanatics who wish to make it big in the industry.
title: Bollywood Diaries

Title: Love Shagun
Cast: Anuj Sachdeva, Nidhi Subbaiah, Manit Joura
overview: J.D., a young man is at an important stage in his life of choosing a life partner.Looking like a plain situation which all youngsters go through, JD is accompanied by an unusual combination of problems, one of a persistent pressure of marriage from his mother and second of the astrological predictions surrounding them. Caught in a fix, JD fights the battle with his three friends, Sandy, Sumit and Deepak who have their own definitions of love. All three friends try different solutions to get JD's life sorted and plan to find a girl for him whom he can divorce. JD in the middle follows all the tricks and plans and ends up meeting Tia, a modern and independent girl who follows her own mind. But much to their surprise, the story unfolds differently and JD finds himself in a larger soup than he had imagined. Between following his mother or his heart, JD is caught in a problem that does not seem to solve.
title: Love Shagun

Title: Tere Bin Laden: Dead or Alive
Cast: Manish Paul, Sikander Kher, Pradhuman Singh, Sugandha Ram
overview: A Bollywood director's plan to use an Osama Bin Laden look-alike in an upcoming film runs afoul of a Taliban arms dealer's desire to show that the terrorist is still alive.
title: Tere Bin Laden Dead or Alive

Title: Zubaan
Cast: Vicky Kaushal, Sarah Jane Dias, Raghav Chanana
overview: A young boy wants to become a big shot but after seeing the bad things involved he instead chooses to pursue his passion that is singing, similar to his father.
title: Zubaan

Title: Jai Gangaajal
Cast: Priyanka Chopra, Anuj Aggarwal, Prakash Jha, Rahul Bhatt
overview: The film features SP Abha Mathur who is appointed the first female SP of Bankipur district, Bihar. She then goes against the Local MLA of Bankipur and henchmen of Lakhisarai district.
title: Jai Gangaajal

Title: Global Baba
Cast: Abhimanyu Singh, Sandeepa Dhar, Ravi Kishan, Pankaj Tripathi, Sanjay Mishra, Akhilendra Mishra
overview: A conman finds refuge in becoming a baba and carries out his various criminal activities under the guise. A policeman, a journalist and politicians get entangled in his Web of deceit.
title: Global Baba

Title: Teraa Surroor
Cast: Himesh Reshammiya, Farah Karimi, Monica Dogra, Naseeruddin Shah, Shekhar Kapur
overview: Tara Wadia (Farah Karimaee), a singer and girlfriend of a gangster Raghu (Himesh Reshammiya) lives with her mother (Shernaz Patel). She goes to Dublin where she gets detained after being caught with drugs. Tara calls Raghua for help now Raghu must help her and find Anirudh Brahman, the stranger who met Tara on Facebook and invited her to Ireland.
title: Teraa Surroor

Title: Kapoor & Sons
Cast: Sidharth Malhotra, Alia Bhatt, Fawad Khan, Rishi Kapoor, Sukant Goel
overview: Returning home to visit their ill grandfather, two estranged brothers must confront their unresolved rivalry while their parents’ marriage frays.
title: Kapoor & Sons

Title: Rocky Handsome
Cast: John Abraham, Shruti Haasan, Nathalia Kaur
overview: A vengeful man embarks on a murderous rampage after the kidnapping of a 7-year-old girl.
title: Rocky Handsome

Title: Ki & Ka
